column.name: FULL_NAME

column.comments: Auto-incrementing primary key

column.name: STORE_ID

table.name: ORDERS
table.comments: Details of who made purchases where

column.name: ORDER_ID
column.comments: Auto-incrementing primary key

column.name: ORDER_TMS
column.comments: When the order was placed

column.name: CUSTOMER_ID
column.comments: Who placed this order

column.name: ORDER_STATUS
column.comments:
What state the order is in. Valid values are:
OPEN - the order is in progress
PAID - money has been received from the customer for this order
SHIPPED - the products have been dispatched to the customer
COMPLETE - the customer has received the order
CANCELLED - the customer has stopped the order
REFUNDED - there has been an issue with the order and the money has been returned to the customer

column.name: STORE_ID
column.comments: Where this order was placed

table.name: ORDER_ITEMS
table.comments: Details of which products the customer has purchased in an order

column.name: ORDER_ID
column.comments: The order these products belong to

column.name: LINE_ITEM_ID
column.comments: An incrementing number, starting at one for each order

column.name: PRODUCT_ID
column.comments: Which item was purchased

column.name: UNIT_PRICE
column.comments: How much the customer paid for one item of the product

column.name: QUANTITY
column.comments: How many items of this product the customer purchased

column.name: SHIPMENT_ID
column.comments: Where this product will be delivered

column.name: PRODUCT_NAME

column.name: UNIT_PRICE

column.name: PRODUCT_DETAILS
column.comments: Further details of the product stored in JSON format

column.name: PRODUCT_IMAGE
column.comments: A picture of the product

column.name: IMAGE_MIME_TYPE
column.comments: The mime-type of the product image

column.name: IMAGE_FILENAME

column.name: IMAGE_CHARSET

column.name: IMAGE_LAST_UPDATED

table.name: SHIPMENTS
table.comments: Details of where ordered goods will be delivered

column.name: SHIPMENT_ID
column.comments: Auto-incrementing primary key

column.name: STORE_ID
column.comments: Which location the goods will be transported from

column.name: CUSTOMER_ID
column.comments: Who this shipment is for

column.name: DELIVERY_ADDRESS
column.comments: Where the goods will be transported to

column.name: SHIPMENT_STATUS
column.comments:
The current status of the shipment. Valid values are:
CREATED - the shipment is ready for order assignment
SHIPPED - the goods have been dispatched
IN-TRANSIT - the goods are en-route to their destination
DELIVERED - the good have arrived at their destination

constraint.name: STORE_AT_LEAST_ONE_ADDRESS_C
constraint.search-condition: web_address IS NOT NULL or physical_address IS NOT NULL

view.name: CUSTOMER_ORDER_PRODUCTS
view.comments: A summary of who placed each order and what they bought
view.complex-attribute: SELECT o.order_id, o.order_tms, o.order_status, c.customer_id, c.email_address, c.full_name, SUM ( oi.quantity * oi.unit_price ) order_total, LISTAGG ( p.product_name, ', ' ON OVERFLOW TRUNCATE '...' WITH COUNT ) WITHIN GROUP ( ORDER BY oi.line_item_id ) items FROM orders o JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id GROUP BY o.order_id, o.order_tms, o.order_status, c.customer_id, c.email_address, c.full_name

column.name: ORDER_ID
column.comments: The primary key of the order

column.name: ORDER_TMS
column.comments: The date and time the order was placed

column.name: ORDER_STATUS
column.comments: The current state of this order

column.name: CUSTOMER_ID
column.comments: The primary key of the customer

column.name: EMAIL_ADDRESS
column.comments: The email address the person uses to access the account

column.name: FULL_NAME
column.comments: What this customer is called

column.name: ORDER_TOTAL
column.comments: The total amount the customer paid for the order

column.name: ITEMS
column.comments: A comma-separated list naming the products in this order

view.name: PRODUCT_ORDERS
view.comments: A summary of the state of the orders placed for each product
view.complex-attribute: SELECT p.product_name, o.order_status, SUM ( oi.quantity * oi.unit_price ) total_sales, COUNT (*) order_count FROM orders o JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id GROUP BY p.product_name, o.order_status

column.name: PRODUCT_NAME
column.comments: What this product is called

column.name: ORDER_STATUS
column.comments: The current state of these order

column.name: TOTAL_SALES
column.comments: The total value of orders placed

column.name: ORDER_COUNT
column.comments: The total number of orders placed

view.name: PRODUCT_REVIEWS
view.comments: A relational view of the reviews stored in the JSON for each product
view.complex-attribute: SELECT p.product_name, r.rating, ROUND ( AVG ( r.rating ) over ( PARTITION BY product_name ), 2 ) avg_rating, r.review FROM products p, JSON_TABLE ( p.product_details, '$' COLUMNS ( NESTED PATH '$.reviews[*]' COLUMNS ( rating INTEGER PATH '$.rating', review VARCHAR2(4000) PATH '$.review' ) ) ) r

column.name: PRODUCT_NAME
column.comments: What this product is called

column.name: RATING
column.comments: The review score the customer has placed. Range is 1-10

column.name: AVG_RATING
column.comments: The mean of the review scores for this product

column.name: REVIEW
column.comments: The text of the review

view.name: STORE_ORDERS
view.comments: A summary of what was purchased at each location, including summaries each store, order status and overall total
view.complex-attribute: SELECT CASE grouping_id ( store_name, order_status ) WHEN 1 THEN 'STORE TOTAL' WHEN 2 THEN 'STATUS TOTAL' WHEN 3 THEN 'GRAND TOTAL' END total, s.store_name, COALESCE ( s.web_address, s.physical_address ) address, s.latitude, s.longitude, o.order_status, COUNT ( DISTINCT o.order_id ) order_count, SUM ( oi.quantity * oi.unit_price ) total_sales FROM stores s JOIN orders o ON s.store_id = o.store_id JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id GROUP BY GROUPING SETS ( ( s.store_name, COALESCE ( s.web_address, s.physical_address ), s.latitude, s.longitude ), ( s.store_name, COALESCE ( s.web_address, s.physical_address ), s.latitude, s.longitude, o.order_status ), o.order_status, () )
